"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-what-time-is-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-friday-26-july\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbWhat time is the Paris Olympics opening ceremony?  Here is the exact time the Paris Olympics opening ceremony will take place, and when you can expect to see SA's 'parade of nations'.  At the beginning of every Olympics, there is always huge interest in the opening ceremony, and it will certainly be interesting to see what has been planned in Paris.  Somewhat strangely, various Olympic events in Paris are already under way, although the opening ceremony will only take place on Friday, 26 July.  The Paris Olympics opening ceremony events are scheduled to begin at 19:30 local time, which is the same as SA time. It will be broadcast on SuperSport's grandstand channel 201, as well as the dedicated main Olympics channel 203.  One of the most popular parts of the opening ceremony sees all participating countries have grand introductions in front of live audiences and millions of spectators across the globe.  Interestingly, the Paris Olympics\\u00a0will see a slight tweak, and instead of athletes walking down a stage, they will be introduced on boats cruising down theRiver Seinein a historic first for a Summer Games.  It should also be noted that South Africa will be the fourth country to appear in the 'parade of nations' because SA is known as Afrique du Sud in French.Akani SimbineandCaitlin Rooskrantzwill be the teamflag bearersfor the Paris Olympics, andMpumelelo MhlongoandKathrine Swanepoelfor the Paralympics.  Here's the full country order for the 2024 Parade of Nations in Paris:  Final additions to the Paris Olympics squad have been made and the names of those added have an asterisk (*) next to them.  AQUATICS (9)Men 